articles.author: Alex Sundby
articles.title: 2024 Miss America crown goes to active-duty U.S. Air Force officer - CBS News
articles.description: U.S. Air Force 2nd Lt. Madison Marsh is the first active-duty service member​ to win the Miss America competition.
articles.content: An officer in the U.S. Air Force was crowned Miss America on Sunday night. Second Lt. Madison Marsh is the first active-duty service member to win the annual competition, according to the Air Force.… [+1882 chars]
